[{"id":"VR814807","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two spheres. Each sphere is positioned at the top of a vertical insulating stand. Sphere X has a charge of positive 2 Q, and Sphere Y has a charge of positive 4 Q.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR814807.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two identical conductive spheres are attached to insulating stands. Sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></span></span> initially has a charge of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive 2 Q\"><math alttext=\"positive 2 Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>Q</mi></math></span></span>, and Sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></math></span></span> initially has a charge of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive 4 Q\"><math alttext=\"positive 4 Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>Q</mi></math></span></span>, as shown in the figure. The two spheres are brought into contact and are then separated. Which of the following correctly compares the change in charge on Sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></span></span> and the change in charge of the two-sphere system?</p><div class=\"table_wrapper\"><table class=\"tgroup align:center cols:3 colsep:0 frame:none rowsep:0\"><col class=\"colspec align:center colname:col1 colnum:1 colsep:1 colwidth:35\"/><col class=\"colspec align:center colname:col2 colnum:2 colwidth:100\"/><col class=\"colspec align:center colname:col3 colnum:3 colwidth:150\"/><thead class=\"thead\"><tr class=\"row rowsep:1\"><th class=\"entry colname:col1\"></th><th class=\"entry colname:col2\">Charge of Sphere <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></span></span></th><th class=\"entry colname:col3\">Net charge of two-sphere system</th></tr></thead><tbody class=\"tbody valign:middle\"><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">A</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\">Increases</td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\">Remains the same</td></tr><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">B</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\">Increases</td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\">Increases</td></tr><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">C</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\">Remains the same</td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\">Remains the same</td></tr><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">D</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\">Remains the same</td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\">Increases</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n","rubricRef":"VR814807_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">A</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">B</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">C</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">D</p>"],"answer":0}]